cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it presents new alternatives to the similarity function for the TextRank algorithm for automatic summarization of texts. It could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) because the TextRank algorithm is often used for information retrieval tasks. Additionally, the paper proposes different functions that achieve a significant improvement, which could fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
